in%20the%20parliament%20caused%20a%20significant%20rupture%20in%20bilateral%20relations%20with%20India%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20expulsion%20of%20an%20Indian%20diplomat%20in%20Ottawa%2C%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCanadian%20security%20agencies%20have%20been%20actively%20pursuing%20credible%20allegations%20of%20a%20potential%20link%20between%20agents%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%26quot%3B%20PM%20Trudeau%20said%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Tuesday%20rejected%20Canada's%20allegations%20of%20Indian%20agents%20being%20involved%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20pro-Khalistan%20leader%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20Khalistan%20Tiger%20Force%20and%20a%20designated%20'terrorist'.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20retaliation%20to%20the%20Trudeau%20administration%20expelling%20an%20Indian%20diplomat%2C%20New%20Delhi%20ordered%20a%20Canadian%20envoy%2C%20believed%20to%20be%20spying%20for%20the%20country%20in%20India%2C%20to%20leave%20within%20five%20days%2C%20the%20Post%20added%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Trudeau%20emphasised%20that%20Canada%20was%20not%20looking%20to%20provoke%20or%20escalate%20the%20situation%2C%20India%20has%20rejected%20its%20accusation%20as%20%26quot%3Babsurd%20and%20motivated%2C%26quot%3B%20shifting%20the%20focus%20to%20Khalistani%20terrorists%20and%20extremists%20sheltered%20in%20Canada%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20seen%20and%20reject%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20their%20Parliament%2C%20as%20also%20the%20statement%20by%20their%20Foreign%20Minister.%20Allegations%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India's%20involvement%20in%20any%20act%20of%20violence%20in%20Canada%20are%20absurd%20and%20motivated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENijjar%20had%20been%20designated%20a%20terrorist%20by%20security%20agencies%20in%202020%20and%20was%20accused%20of%20supporting%20attacks%20in%20Punjab%2C%20the%20report%20noted%2C%20adding%20that%20India%20sought%20his%20extradition%20in%202022%20and%20linked%20him%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Hindu%20priest%20in%20Punjab%20that%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20India%20had%20been%20pressuring%20countries%20like%20Canada%2C%20Australia%2C%20Britain%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20which%20have%20significant%20Sikh%20communities%2C%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20the%20Khalistan%20movement.%20Pro-Khalistan%20protests%20had%20taken%20place%20in%20London%20and%20San%20Francisco%2C%20causing%20tension%20with%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20diplomatic%20controversy%20unfolds%20as%20Western%20nations%20seek%20to%20strengthen%20their%20geopolitical%20and%20trade%20partnerships%20with%20India%20while%20refraining%20from%20criticizing%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi's%20authoritarian%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMichael%20Kugelman%2C%20a%20South%20Asia%20analyst%2C%20pointed%20out%20the%20dilemma%20facing%20Western%20governments%2C%20acknowledging%20Canada%20as%20an%20ally%20but%20valuing%20their%20relationship%20with%20India%20as%20a%20key%20strategic%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post%2C%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20India%20in%20September%20was%20marked%20by%20tension%2C%20with%20Trudeau%20sidelined%20and%20denied%20formal%20bilateral%20talks%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi.%20The%20Khalistan%20issue%20was%20discussed%20on%20the%20summit's%20sidelines%2C%20further%20straining%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanada's%20Foreign%20Minister%20Melanie%20Joly%20stated%20that%20Trudeau%20had%20raised%20the%20allegations%20with%20President%20Biden%20and%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20with%20the%20topic%20expected%20to%20be%20discussed%20at%20the%20U