%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66856568.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66856568.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Many%20Times%20Has%20India%20Expelled%20Diplomats%20From%20Western%20Countries%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19221735%2Fcanadian-flag-1229484_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20diplomatic%20practice%2C%20the%20expulsion%20of%20diplomats%20is%20considered%20an%20extreme%20measure.%20For%20India%2C%20it%20is%20even%20more%20unusual%20to%20resort%20to%20this%20action%20against%20Western%20nations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20India%20announced%20that%20a%20senior%20Canadian%20diplomat%20was%20asked%20to%20leave%20within%20five%20days%20in%20a%20tit-for-tat%20measure%20after%20an%20Indian%20high%20commission%20official%20was%20expelled%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20declared%20that%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%E2%80%9D%20allegations%20linking%20the%20government%20of%20India%20to%20the%20death%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20and%20Pakistan%20have%20periodically%20expelled%20diplomats%20from%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20nations%2C%20with%20the%20most%20recent%20instance%20occurring%20in%20August%202019.%20During%20this%20recent%20episode%2C%20both%20countries%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Farticle-370-kashmir-pakistan-downgrade-diplomatic-ties-india%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpelled%20their%20high%20commissioners%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20downgraded%20diplomatic%20relations%20following%20the%20changes%20made%20to%20the%20status%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20within%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20there%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-53156264%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanother%20round%20of%20expulsions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20the%20staff%20in%20the%20embassies%20were%20further%20whittled%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20dismissal%20of%20diplomats%20from%20Western%20countries%20is%20relatively%20rare%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20diplomatic%20history.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Findia-expels-senior-us-diplomat-who-helped-devyani-khobragades-maid%2Farticleshow%2F28647754.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENine%20years%20ago%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20towards%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20Manmohan%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20second%20term%2C%20India%20asked%20the%20United%20States%20to%20withdraw%20a%20diplomat%20in%20the%20New%20Delhi%20embassy.%20The%20announcement%20was%20made%20just%20as%20Indian%20diplomat%20Devyani%20Khobragade%20was%20on%20a%20plane%20back%20after%20the%20US%20state%20department%20told%20her%20to%20leave%20the%20US%20after%20she%20was%20indicted%20by%20a%20jury%20in%20New%20York%20for%20alleged%20visa%20fraud%20in%20January%202014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reciprocal%20expulsions%20had%20marked%20the%20lowest%20point%20in%20India-US%20relations%2C%20which%20was%20triggered%20by%20the%20strip-and-search%20of%20Khobragade%20for%20allegedly%20underpaying%20her%20maid%2C%20Sangeeta%20Richard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20relations%20with%20India%20were%20soon%20brought%20back%20to%20the%20rails%20when%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20was%20invited%20by%20US%20President%20Barack%20Obama%20after%20the%202014%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20another%20Western%20nation%20with%20whom%20India%20has%20a%20very%20close%20partnership%20had%20its%20top%20diplomat%20expelled%20about%2035%20years%20back.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20early%201985%2C%20the%20corridors%20of%20South%20Block%20were%20rocked%20by%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Clargest%20spy%20scandals%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20history%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20resulted%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20Salman%20Haidar%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-1985-02-03-mn-13237-story.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannouncing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20India%20had%20ordered%20the%20French%20ambassador%20Serge%20Boidevaix%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20within%2030%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20India%20did%20not%20give%20any%20reason%20for%20the%20expulsion%2C%20contemporary%20media%20reports%20said%20that%20it%20was%20related%20to%20the%20discovery%20of%20a%20spy%20network%20which%20revolved%20around%20private%20secretaries%20at%20key%20ministries%20who%20passed%20on%20official%20secrets%20to%20an%20Indian%20businessman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20a%20UPI%20report%2C%20it%20was%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfirst%20time%20that%20such%20a%20high-ranking%20diplomat%20has%20been%20told%20to%20leave%20India%20in%20connection%20with%20espionage%20involving%20both%20military%20and%20industrial%20secrets%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20spy%20ring%20that%20led%20to%20the%20expulsion%20of%20the%20French%20ambassador%20had%20allegedly%20penetrated%20the%20office%20of%20then%20principal%20secretary%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20P.C.%20Alexander.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20month%20earlier%20in%20January%201985%2C%20the%20French%20deputy%20military%20attache%2C%20Lt.%20Col.%20Alain%20Bolley%2C%20who%20was%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20spy%20ring%2C%20was%20withdrawn%20from%20his%20post%20in%20the%20New%20Delhi%20embassy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20a%20recently%20published%20book%20by%20veteran%20Indian%20diplomat%20C.R.%20Gharekhan%2C%20while%20the%20French%20connection%20in%20the%20spy%20network%20got%20the%20most%20attention%2C%20New%20Delhi%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1050786%2Fan-advisor-to-former-pm-rajiv-gandhi-recalls-how-a-1985-espionage-scandal-rocked-indian-politics%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Equietly%20expelled%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20diplomats%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20Poland%20and%20East%20Germany.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGharekhan%20wrote%20that%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20regretted%20that%20he%20had%20dealt%20with%20the%20French%20%E2%80%9Ctoo%20harshly%E2%80%9D.%20There%20were%20efforts%20to%20bring%20back%20relations%20to%20a%20keel%2C%20which%20included%20early%20approval%20for%20the%20new%20French%20ambassador.%20India%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fmagazine%2Finternational%2Fstory%2F19850331-rajiv-gandhi-visit-to-paris-likely-to-put-derailed-indo-french-ties-back-on-track-769897-2013-12-03%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannounced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20Gandhi%20will%20travel%20to%20France%20to%20take%20part%20in%20the%20inauguration%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Year%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20which%20was%20earlier%20planned%20to%20have%20been%20kicked%20off%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20Francois%20Mitterand.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20public%20announcements%20were%20made%20by%20the%20MEA%20in%20the%20above%20two%20cases%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20a%20more%20recent%20incident%20between%20Germany%20and%20India%2C%20where%20both%20countries%20expelled%20diplomatic%20officers%20but%20without%20any%20fanfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20first%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Ftrial-of-raw-agent-in-german-court-casts-spotlight-on-indias-secret-war-against-khalistan-terror-in-europe-2624861.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%20News%2018%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20was%20related%20to%20the%20impending%20trial%20of%20a%20Frankfurt%20resident%20who%20received%20payoffs%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20external%20intelligence%20agency%2C%20the%20Research%20and%20Analysis%20Wing%2C%20for%20%E2%80%9Cspying%20on%20Khalistan%20and%20Kashmiri%20secessionists%E2%80%9D%20in%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20article%2C%20the%20officer%20was%20recruited%20into%20R%26amp%3BAW%20from%20the%20Indian%20Revenue%20Service%20and%20was%20operating%20out%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20consulate%20in%20Frankfurt.%20He%20was%20asked%20to%20leave%20for%20indulging%20in%20espionage.%20In%20a%20tit-for-tat%20move%2C%20a%20German%20diplomat%20was%20asked%20to%20leave%20India.%20However%2C%20because%20there%20was%20no%20announcement%20of%20the%20expulsions%2C%20there%20is%20no%20official%20confirmation%20of%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695142819000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19221735%2Fcanadian-flag-1229484_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-expel-diplomats-western-countries%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20Delhi%20responded%20in%20kind%20after%20Canada%20expelled%20an%20Indian%20diplomat%20following%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20claim%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20was%20behind%20the%20assassination%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-expel-diplomats-western-countries%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ganesh%20Chaturthi%3A%20Anushka%2C%20Kohli%20Perform%20Puja%3B%20Karisma%20Has%20Special%20Message%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFresh%20from%20the%20Asia%20Cup%20triumph%2C%20the%20Indian%20cricket%20team%20is%20enjoying%20a%20mini-break%20before%20the%20India%20vs%20Australia%20ODI%20