p%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20household%20debt%20has%20increased.%20%3Cem%3EFE%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20stock%20of%20financial%20liabilities%2C%20household%20debt%20consequently%20remained%20sharply%20elevated%20at%2037.6%25%20of%20GDP%20in%20FY23%2C%20as%20against%2036.9%25%20in%20FY22.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdding%20to%20these%20pressures%2C%20wages%20have%20not%20risen%20amid%20high%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFalling%20or%20stagnant%20wages%20coupled%20with%20high%20inflation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20of%20high%20inflation%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20significant%20growth%20in%20real%20wages%20at%20the%20all-India%20level%20over%20the%20past%20eight%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20healthcare%20and%20education%20is%20rising%2C%20most%20of%20which%20has%20to%20be%20borne%20privately.%20In%202021%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20medical%20inflation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fcost-of-treatment-doubles-in-5-years-as-medical-inflation-bites%2Farticleshow%2F102961777.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ewas%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2012%25%20%E2%80%93%20the%20highest%20among%20all%20Asian%20countries.%20The%20cost%20of%20treatment%20has%20doubled%20in%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fbanking-and-finance%2Feducation-inflation-tips-to-invest-for-children-education-8880375%2F%5C%22%3Eeducation%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20been%20significantly%20high%20at%2011-12%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20falling%20or%20stagnant%20household%20incomes%2C%20amid%20high%20inflation%2C%20is%20probably%20the%20main%20reason%20for%20the%20subdued%20savings%20and%20higher%20borrowings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20RBI%20data%20on%20household%20assets%20and%20liabilities%20also%20raise%20worries%20about%20the%20immediate%20growth%20potential%20of%20the%20economy.%20The%20support%20to%20growth%20from%20private%20consumption%20may%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20weaker%20than%20anticipated%2C%20even%20as%20a%20private%20capex%20cycle%20appears%20to%20be%20delayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENikhil%20Gupta%2C%20economist%20at%20Motilal%20Oswal%2C%20told%3Cem%3E%20FE%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20combination%20of%20weak%20income%20growth%20and%20falling%20financial%20savings%2C%20led%20by%20borrowings%2C%20is%20unsustainable.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20that%20consumption%20growth%20is%20unsustainable.%20Whether%20it%20will%20be%20substituted%20by%20investments%20is%20not%20our%20base%20case%2C%20though%20the%20jury%20is%20still%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695113433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fhousehold-savings-fall-to-five-decade-low-in-fy23-debt-remains-sharply-elevated-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20indicates%20that%20households%20have%20been%20largely%20borrowing%20to%20fulfil%20their%20consumption%20needs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fhousehold-savings-fall-to-five-decade-low-in-fy23-debt-remains-sharply-elevated-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22American%20prisoners%20freed%20by%20Iran%20head%20to%20US%20after%20choreographed%20swap%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695112549000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103779686%2Cimgsize-39920.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Famerican-prisoners-freed-by-iran-head-to-us-after-choreographed-swap%2Farticleshow%2F103779003.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D