.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20village%20was%20facing%20a%20water%20crisis%20due%20to%20which%20farming%20was%20becoming%20increasingly%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20entire%20village%2C%20which%20has%20around%2040%20farmers%2C%20was%20getting%20water%20from%20one%20small%20dam.%20We%20worked%20on%20a%20programme%20that%20would%20optimise%20water%20usage%20and%20increase%20water%20availability%20in%20the%20village.%20We%20did%20a%20detailed%20soil%20and%20water%20assessment%2C%20and%20worked%20on%20an%20equitable%20water%20distribution%20model.%20We%20also%20helped%20villagers%20regulate%20water%20usage%20so%20that%20they%20receive%20water%20even%20during%20summer%20months%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20the%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharmila%20continued%20her%20work%20across%20Maharashtra%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20and%20Gujarat.%20In%20Dungarpur%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20she%20helped%20farmers%20move%20from%20farming%20just%20one%20crop%20%E2%80%94%20corn%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F327249%2Fkota-engineer-runs-sustainable-dairy-farm-saves-on-electricy-bills-gau-organics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20crops%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCrops%20like%20maize%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20water.%20So%20we%20helped%20the%20tribal%20farmers%20in%20Dungarpurby%20showing%20them%20how%20to%20cultivate%20crops%20like%20%3Cem%3Emoong%20%3C%2Fem%3E(green%20gram)%20using%20less%20water%20on%20their%20farms%20%E2%80%94%20through%20a%20partnership%20with%20ITC%E2%80%99s%20e-Choupal.%20This%20way%2C%20the%20farmers%20always%20have%20a%20backup%20crop%20in%20case%20one%20fails.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20they%20also%20gained%20access%20to%20ITC%E2%80%99s%20marketplace.%20We%20also%20assisted%20farmers%20in%20growing%20millets%2C%20which%20require%20less%20water%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDipti%2C%20a%20farmer%20from%20Dungarpur%2C%20says%20they%20have%20benefited%20from%20this%20programme%2C%20and%20that%20today%2C%20they%20also%20grow%20vegetables.%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20my%20husband%20would%20have%20to%20go%20to%20other%20cities%20in%20search%20of%20work%20if%20our%20crop%20failed.%20Now%2C%20as%20we%20are%20growing%20lentils%20and%20vegetables%2C%20we%20are%20able%20to%20sustain%20ourselves%20well.%20We%20are%20able%20to%20manage%20even%20with%20less%20water%2C%20as%20we%20have%20a%20multitude%20of%20crops%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EUnleashing%20the%20magic%20of%20millet%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20540px)%20100vw%2C%20540px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsharmila-nd-son-1694440927.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sharmila%20has%20started%20Gud%20Mom%20with%20her%20son%20Shubham%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsharmila-nd-son-1694440927.jpeg%20540w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsharmila-nd-son-1694440927-167x300.jpeg%20167w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsharmila-nd-son-1694440927-500x896.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsharmila-nd-son-1694440927-150x269.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-329602%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22968%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESharmila%20started%20%E2%80%98Gud%20Mom%E2%80%99%20with%20her%20son%20Shubham%20to%20sell%20millet-based%20products.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20Sharmila%20says%20they%20have%20helped%20over%201.5%20lakh%20farmers%20in%20five%20states%20through%20water%20management%20programmes%2C%20millet%20and%20vegetable%20cultivation%2C%20and%20capacity-building%